caption: The smoke ugh! Couldn't enjoy anything cigarette smoke was awful. People was just constantly chain smoking, one table with four smokers all smoking-constantly. You should really consider separating the outside from the inside. Dining inside no one wants to smell cigarettes while dining. We even asked if they could close the garage door opening. No luck. What a terrible experience,we all left with a headache.

Cool place to hang and watch a game. Open aired with garage type doors, lots of tvs. Had the pizza, was good with a cold beer. Definitely a locals spot with temp screenings and they clean. I'll be back. They do the QR code ordering but can also order from a person.
I had an amazing  at this place. We loved the wonderful atmosphere and the meals. The staff members are super amiable. I’m happy we ultimately decided to visit here.

We were seated for about 10 minutes and the waiter told us he'd be with us in a few and 20 minutes later we still sitting without drinks or food.. We watched another table walk in and get served right away.The restaurant wasn't busy. I use to love the place and used to be a regular but unfortunately this isn't the first time we have had to wait for service. Sadly disappointed😔

My food was not good at all. The cheesy waffle fries was not cheesy, fries were dry and cold, pulled pork was dry and stuck together, didn't know can make a bad pulled pork sandwich. Ate the pickles. Not a fan of their fried oreo, batter was eeehh.  Luckily the other order of wings and the burger came out well. Which is why I gave a 2 star.  Staff was friendly, did a pick up order. There was a good crowd there so this place maybe good for quick bite and drinks; like a burger and beer.

Due to COVID, they only have online menus. They're google menu is drastically different prices than the website. The server was unable to explain and answer simple questions so we thought we ordered one thing and got something else. The owner was not friendly when we had an issue with our bill because we were charged $22 for a burger that says is $13 on Google menu. But apparently it was our fault. It is probably a good dive bar for drinks but that is it in my personal experience. We tried to be understanding and would have been fine despite everything that was wrong but there was no customer service and that ruined the experience for me.

I witnessed great service,  and a nice touch on free refills of soda.  Stay away from sugar, self!  Really enjoyed my experiences and I will be back.

I appreciate business's like such and hope they stick around for many more years.

I LOVE CADDIES!!!  Been coming here for years and will continue.  This place is the Cheers of Bethesda. Everyone is friendly and inviting and will eventually know your name!!   The menu is trendy and the staff even makes you comfortable.  The perfect happy hour spot after a long day in the office where you can shoot your shot or BUY SHOTS!!  Tuesday trivia is loads of fun.  Today, I just had a craving for the tots with crab and placed the order to go. Upon arrival, I found a spot right out front so, decided to dine in and treat myself to a cocktail.

A pretty decent sports bar in the Bethesda area. Not a bad place to go to, but there are better sports bars nearby. I came to Caddies on Cordell Wednesday for their "Comedy at Caddies" night because i had seen their flyer posted somewhere online. It was an open Mic comedy show so anyone could sign up. They also had musical bingo downstairs where you  cross out the box of the song that is played. Getting BINGO gets you gift cards to use at their establishment. I did not try their food, but their drinks were reasonably priced. As mentioned above, there are better sports bars nearby, but if you are looking for something a little more laid back, caddies is an "ok" spot to try.

It's a sports bar, but there are better ones in the Rockville/Bethesda area. The drinks are relatively weak when you consider what you're paying for them, and every surface is just a little bit sticky.  They have live music on the weekends, which is a huge plus, but sometimes the bands are downright unpleasant.  Still, if you're in downtown Bethesda and want something more laid back, this is a good go-to.

Overall a meh experience. The service was spotty at best and our server never checked in with our table. I had to go to the bar to place my order, and we had to flag someone down in a different room to get refills on our drinks. The food was wholly acceptable bar food, but nothing outstanding. The onion rings and Fries were good, the wings wore a bit dry But had a decent flavor. We found the sliders to be above-average, but the pickles were a little soggy.  At around 10 p.m., they walled our section off, put a wet floor sign next to my seat, and wheeled out a mop bucket full of disinfectant and parked it a few feet from our table. This was not really an appetizing end to our evening.

My wife and I have been on a fun little kick of trying the exact same menu items at places and comparing them.  Caddies had some of the best stuff so far.  The Buffalo chicken,  bbq pork, and French dip were better than other places we've tried (including ale house and tgif).  The pizza was just "okay"... After having two gourmet pizza places this week,  I'd say unless you are really in a pizza mood, skip it and go for the standard "bar food" which is really good.  The drinks specials were average.  We liked our server,  she conversed with us enough for us to enjoy it without overdoing it and she was good at checking in on us.  There is definitely a "pub" smell when you first walk in.
